did.abstract: The materials consist of lantern slides maintained by the Peabody Museum of Natural History at Yale University documenting North American vegetation and habitats.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Forms part of Yale Record Group 33-A (YRG 33-A), Records of the Peabody Museum.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Peabody Museum of Natural History, Yale University, Botanical Teaching Slides (RU 93). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The materials consist of lantern slides maintained by the Peabody Museum of Natural History at Yale University documenting North American vegetation and habitats.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The materials are arranged alphabetically by specimen or geographic location.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Note: number in the folder column refers to slide code number.
